The interview with an industry professional helped me understand how both behavioural skills and technical knowledge play an important role in achieving success in the IT industry. As a student studying computer science, most of our focus is usually on learning programming languages, algorithms, and technical concepts. However, after conducting this interview, I realized that technical skills alone are not enough to succeed in a professional environment. Behavioural skills such as communication, curiosity, teamwork, and adaptability are equally important for long-term growth in the technology sector.

During the interview, the professional explained that their career journey started through campus placement opportunities and internships. In the beginning stages of their career, they worked on backend development using technologies such as Java and Spring Boot. They also gained early exposure to professional environments through internships and training programs. These experiences helped them understand how technical knowledge learned in college is actually applied in real projects. According to the interviewee, practical exposure is very important because it helps students move from theoretical learning to real-world problem solving.

One important insight from the interview was that the right attitude towards learning is one of the most valuable qualities in the IT industry. The interviewee mentioned that nobody expects fresh graduates to know everything from the first day of work. Instead, companies value employees who are willing to learn, ask questions, and improve themselves continuously. Curiosity and the willingness to explore new technologies can help engineers stay relevant in a field that is constantly evolving.

Another behavioural skill that the interviewee emphasized was the importance of being a good listener. In the workplace, engineers often work with team members who have different levels of experience and different technical expertise. Listening carefully to seniors and colleagues helps in understanding project requirements and learning from their experience. This also helps avoid misunderstandings and improves collaboration within the team.

Communication is another key factor that contributes to success in the IT industry. Software development is rarely an individual task. Most projects are developed by teams consisting of developers, managers, designers, testers, and sometimes clients. Clear communication ensures that everyone understands the objectives of the project and the responsibilities of each team member. If communication is poor, even technically strong teams may face problems in delivering successful projects.

The interview also highlighted the importance of teamwork in modern technology companies. Many organizations follow a team-based structure where tasks are distributed among multiple developers. Each member contributes their expertise to complete the project efficiently. In such environments, professionals must respect each other’s knowledge and work collaboratively. Behavioural qualities such as patience, empathy, and professionalism help maintain a positive work environment.

Another topic discussed during the interview was leadership and workplace hierarchy. According to the interviewee, many modern organizations try to reduce strict hierarchical barriers and encourage open interaction between team members. Team leaders guide the development process and provide support to junior employees. Interns and fresh graduates are encouraged to ask questions and seek help whenever needed. This approach helps new employees learn faster and feel comfortable within the organization.

The interview also provided insight into how professionals manage workplace pressure and deadlines. In the technology industry, projects often have strict deadlines, and engineers must work efficiently to deliver results on time. Behavioural skills such as persistence, time management, and professionalism play a significant role in handling such situations. Breaking complex work into smaller tasks and coordinating with team members helps reduce pressure and improve productivity.

One interesting point mentioned by the interviewee was that professionals should avoid getting involved in workplace politics, especially at the beginning of their careers. Instead, fresh employees should focus on learning, understanding the work culture, and building positive relationships with their colleagues. Maintaining professionalism and respect towards others helps create a healthy working environment.

Another important lesson from the interview was the importance of balancing technical and interpersonal development. Many students spend most of their time focusing only on technical preparation such as coding and data structures. While these skills are essential, it is also necessary to develop communication skills, teamwork abilities, and problem-solving mindset. Engineers who combine technical expertise with strong interpersonal abilities are more likely to grow into leadership roles in the future.

The interviewee also mentioned that a person’s reputation in an organization depends not only on their technical performance but also on their behaviour and work ethic. Employees who communicate well, respect their teammates, and show dedication to their work are usually trusted with greater responsibilities. Over time, these qualities help individuals progress in their careers.

From my perspective as a student, this interview was a valuable learning experience. It helped me understand that preparing for a career in technology requires more than just learning programming languages. Developing curiosity, maintaining professionalism, and learning to work effectively with others are equally important skills. These qualities help engineers adapt to changing technologies and complex workplace environments.

In conclusion, the interview clearly showed that behavioural skills and technical skills together form the foundation for success in the IT industry. Technical knowledge allows professionals to design and build systems, while behavioural skills help them collaborate, communicate, and grow within organizations. For students preparing to enter the technology field, focusing on both areas is essential. By combining strong technical foundations with effective communication, teamwork, and adaptability, individuals can build successful and meaningful careers in the rapidly evolving world of technology.
